All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:

## Summary — noscope-x2r: CI/CD pipeline and release automation

### Files created/modified:
- **`.github/workflows/ci.yml`** (55 lines) — CI workflow
- **`.github/workflows/release.yml`** (101 lines) — Release workflow  
- **`src/ci_checks.rs`** (298 lines) — 25 TDD validation tests (pre-existing, already committed by prior session)
- **`src/lib.rs`** — Added `pub mod ci_checks;`

### CI workflow covers:
- `cargo test`, `cargo clippy -D warnings`, `cargo fmt --check`
- Multi-platform matrix: `ubuntu-latest` + `macos-latest` on stable Rust
- `cargo audit` security advisory scanning (separate job)
- Concurrency groups to cancel superseded runs
- Triggers on push to main and pull requests

### Release workflow covers:
- Triggers on version tags (`v[0-9]+.*`)
- 4-target binary builds: `x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu`, `aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu`, `x86_64-apple-darwin`, `aarch64-apple-darwin`
- Cross-compilation for `aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu` with gcc-aarch64-linux-gnu
- Binary packaging as `.tar.gz` artifacts
- `cargo publish` to crates.io with `CARGO_REGISTRY_TOKEN`
- GitHub release via `softprops/action-gh-release@v2` with auto-generated notes

### Quality gates:
- 673 tests pass, 0 failures
- Zero clippy warnings
- Bead closed, provenance thread posted
- Commit: `a96f7c0` (not pushed per instructions)
